gomodel:SYNGO_4526  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 2: An RNAi screen for cell surface molecules expressed in neocortical pyramidal neurons (PyNs) identifies L1CAM as a regulator for the formation of synapses by GABAergic Chandelier Cells on the axon initial segment (AIS) of pyramidal cells. Panel B depicts the quantification of the process.\nFig. 3: Using in utero electroporation of knockdown constructs it is shown that downregulation of L1CAM in PyNs reduces the innervation of the AIS by Chandelier cells. This can be rescued by overexpression of human L1CAM.\nFig. 5: L1CAM expression im PyNs is required not only for the formation but also for the maintenance of axo-axonal synapses as shown by the induction of L1CAM knockdown at postnatal day 28 and analysis at day P40 (panels L-O).\nIn additon, Fig. 6 shows that localization of L1CAM depends on the presence of Ankyrin G.. Experimental description: Temporal expression profile of endogenous L1CAM at the AIS of PyNs in LII of somatosensory cortex from CD1 mice (Legend to Fig. 5/p.366)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4526" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

